  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0db6\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda \u0dbb\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2?",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Will the country close next week?",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Although it has not been officially decided by the government, it is reported that there is a risk of the country being locked down next week due to the fuel crisis.",
        "As the fuel crisis has affected the country to the extent that it is not even possible to maintain the essential services, it is also known that this risky situation will continue until the fuel is imported.",
        "The fuel crisis has worsened to the extent that not only the public transport services buses, but also essential services such as health services and education cannot be maintained.",
        "Moreover, there is currently a situation where it is not possible to provide enough fuel for ambulance services and medical supply services in hospitals. Although the government provided limited fuel to essential services last week, many essential services were disrupted last week as well.",
        "In this situation, it has been learned that there has been a serious crisis in maintaining the country's affairs as normal for the next week.",
        "The government recently announced that a diesel ship will arrive in Sri Lanka next week and a petrol ship on the 22nd of next week."
      ],
